<p>The <code>replace</code> function replaces all occurrences of a substring.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'hello world' | replace('world', 'there'){close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo 'hello world' | replace('world', 'there')}</b></p>

<h2>Remove Characters</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'a-b-c-d' | replace('-', ''){close}</pre>
<p>No dashes: <b>{echo 'a-b-c-d' | replace('-', '')}</b></p>

<h2>Change Separators</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'one_two_three' | replace('_', ' '){close}</pre>
<p>Spaces: <b>{echo 'one_two_three' | replace('_', ' ')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $email | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Name from email: <b>{echo $email | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'Hello World' | lower | replace(' ', '-'){close}</pre>
<p>Slug: <b>{echo 'Hello World' | lower | replace(' ', '-')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'a.b.c' | replace('.', '/') | replace('a', 'x'){close}</pre>
<p>Multiple replacements: <b>{echo 'a.b.c' | replace('.', '/') | replace('a', 'x')}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Replaces ALL occurrences. For removing text, you can also use <code>cut</code>.</p>
